{"type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Geographic Clustering + Nearest Neighbor ★ Recommended\n      How it works: Plants are first grouped geographically into clusters (one cluster per available working day) using k-means. Each cluster then becomes a day's work. Google Maps Distance Matrix is used to get real driving times between all plants, and Nearest Neighbor TSP orders the stops within each day starting from the technician's start address.\n      \n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Much better route quality than A\n            Geographic clustering minimizes daily travel\n            Real driving times from Google Maps\n            Reasonable implementation complexity\n            Travel time cache in DB (no repeated API calls)\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            k-means can produce uneven clusters\n            Not globally optimal (still heuristic)\n            More Maps API calls upfront\n          \n        \n      \n      Effort 4–5 days dev  |  Route quality ★★★☆","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1774707930978}
